Civil Society Organizations (CSOs) under the aegis of Benue Coalition Against Rape yesterday staged a peaceful protest over the increase in the rape of minors at the Benue South Senatorial district. Addressing the protesters who came out in their large numbers in Otukpo  local government, headquarters of the zone to protest the rape of a 14 year old Ene Odeh who was raped recently by the state secretary of All Progressive Grand Alliance (APGA), Eddy Ujah now at large, the convener of the protest Yemi Itodo lamented that over eight cases of rape were reported in the area within a week. According to him, the rate at which men are defiling minors in the state especially in Zone C is alarming, that is why the CSOs, are out in their numbers to say no to the menace of rape in Benue and Nigeria at large. In an interview with the founder, Restorer of Paths Care Foundation, Evangelist Enuwa Soo, who  said she was a caregiver to the late Ochanya who died two years ago on the account of rape said it is high time government at all level protect the girl child. She lamented the delay in getting justice for rape victims saying that two years after the death of Ochanya, the case is still in the court, and the delay is emboldening some men to commit similar crime thinking that nothing will be done.